
[1]bufonite

   BU'FONITE, n. [L. bufo, a toad.] Toadstone, or fossil-teeth of the
   anarrhicas or sea-wolf, formerly much esteemed for its imaginary
   virtues and worn in rings. It was named from an opinion that it was
   found in the head of a toad.
